# Runtime Testing Rules

- If code changes require restarting frontend or backend to verify behavior, restart them automatically.
- Before starting a dev server, check whether the target port is already occupied by an old instance of the same project.
- If the expected port is occupied, stop the old process first, then restart on the same intended port.
- Do not keep switching ports just to work around stale local processes unless the user explicitly asks for a different port.
- When testing depends on a restarted server, confirm the final frontend/backend URLs in the reply.
- Prefer keeping frontend and backend URLs stable during a debugging session.
